abstract: The U.S. trade deficit fell for the first time in six years in 2019 as President Donald Trump hammered China with import taxes.
snippet: The U.S. trade deficit fell for the first time in six years in 2019 as President Donald Trump hammered China with import taxes.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. trade deficit fell for the first time in six years in 2019 as President Donald Trump hammered China with import taxes.
headline_main: US Trade Deficit Drops 1.7% Last Year to $616.8 Billion
headline_print_headline: US Trade Deficit Drops 1.7% Last Year to $616.8 Billion

abstract: New trade data for 2019 reflects a cooling economy and a year of aggressive trade clashes, particularly with China.
snippet: New trade data for 2019 reflects a cooling economy and a year of aggressive trade clashes, particularly with China.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The overall United States trade deficit shrank last year for the first time in six years as the American economy cooled, domestic oil production soared and President Trump waged an aggressive global trade war to rewrite America’s trading terms.

abstract: The dispute over the outcome of September’s presidential race is playing out while sensitive peace talks take place between the U.S. and the Taliban.
snippet: The dispute over the outcome of September’s presidential race is playing out while sensitive peace talks take place between the U.S. and the Taliban.
lead_paragraph: KABUL, Afghanistan — More than four months after Afghans cast their votes for a new president amid a raging war, the crisis over the election’s results deepened as officials on Wednesday ordered a partial audit of a decisive share of ballots.

abstract: Democrat Kweisi Mfume says that if he regains the seat in Congress he once held in a heavily Democratic Baltimore area district, cutting violent crime in the city and its suburbs will be his top concern.
snippet: Democrat Kweisi Mfume says that if he regains the seat in Congress he once held in a heavily Democratic Baltimore area district, cutting violent crime in the city and its suburbs will be his top concern.
lead_paragraph: BALTIMORE — Democrat Kweisi Mfume says that if he regains the seat in Congress he once held in a heavily Democratic Baltimore area district, cutting violent crime in the city and its suburbs will be his top concern.
headline_main: Baltimore's Problems in Focus as Primary Winners Look Ahead
